renames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Baschi","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Indian and Bangladeshi: Barendra Brahmin habitational name from Bagcha, a village near Barackpore in West Bengal."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Neri","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Respelling of either   Kerry   or  <b>Ceri</b>  ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Neri Di Baschi was born about 1148, in Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Italy. She had at least 1 son with Neri Di Baschi."},"et":{"ABT 1148–":"umbes 1148–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1148":"1148","ABT 1148":"umbes 1148","1140":"1140","ABT 1170":"umbes 1170","1170":"1170","BASCHI,, IT":"Baschi, Terni, Umbria, Itaalia"},"fi":{"ABT 1148–":"no